The two police officers have been detained at the Gigiri Police Station. [File, Standard]  Two police officers have been arrested for attempting to rob a Dagoretti resident.  It is alleged the officers, who were armed with pistols, attempted to rob Stephen Kamotho Kinyanjui whom they had handcuffed. The incident happened on Thursday, September 9 at Kioko area in Dagoretti, Nairobi.  “The man resisted [the robbery attempt] and shouted for help (sic). Members of the public intervened and rescued him,” says a report filed at the Gigiri Police Station.  The two officers, both attached to Spring Valley Police Station, however managed to escape.  Gang targeting schools, hotels and bars killed 13 in last one year  Woman snatches AK-47 rifle from robber, rescues self and husband  Four found guilty of robbery with violence, sentenced to death   How man walked to freedom thanks to conflicting laws While fleeing the scene, a pocket phone belonging to one of the suspects fell.  Officers from Kikuyu Police Station retrieved the phone, and used it in identifying the suspects.  A subsequent search for the suspects was launched, leading to their arrest on Thursday morning.  A Jericho pistol loaded with 15 bullets and a Ceska pistol with an equal number of ammunition were recovered from the suspects.  “They (suspects) have been detained at the Gigiri Police Station awaiting collection by DCI officers from Kikuyu station,” said the report.   3 prisoners serving life sentences make a daring escape from the Kamiti Maximum Security Prison  Stripping suspects face death penalty after they were charged with robbery with violence and sexual   MSETO WA KAUNTI; Mshukiwa wa wizi wa magari akamatwa mjini Kitengela By Josphat Thiong’o | 1 day ago By Paul Ogemba | 1 day ago By Kamore Maina | 1 day ago By Josphat Thiong’o | 1 day ago